  "texts": [
    "Fairness in healthcare is about providing equitable access to care, resources, and outcomes for all patients, regardless of their background or social status.",
    "In AI-driven healthcare, achieving fairness requires developing algorithms that are free from bias and capable of delivering accurate diagnoses and treatments to all patient groups 63.",
    "Biases can arise from data used to train AI, the design of algorithms, and the ways in which healthcare professionals and patients interact with AI systems.",
    "To address these challenges, it is essential to use diverse and representative data, conduct regular audits, and provide education to clinicians and patients on potential biases and how to navigate them 63.",
